1
00:00:03,976 --> 00:00:23,976
Officail Website : kissasian.be  Translate by =Qari= @Team Viki

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:08,320
[Episode 1]

3
00:00:14,560 --> 00:00:17,016
You don't have to sacrifice
this much for me.

4
00:00:17,040 --> 00:00:19,480
If we pretend to be a couple,
we need to make it real.

5
00:00:21,080 --> 00:00:24,096
How can we fool those people
watching outside?

6
00:00:24,120 --> 00:00:27,056
Helping you is also helping myself.

7
00:00:27,080 --> 00:00:28,960
Otherwise, we'll both die here.

8
00:00:33,360 --> 00:00:35,816
I don't even know who you are.

9
00:00:35,840 --> 00:00:37,496
Once we leave this place,

10
00:00:37,520 --> 00:00:39,776
we'll never see each other again.

11
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:41,720
You don't need to know who I am.

12
00:00:45,520 --> 00:00:47,456
I will definitely

13
00:00:47,480 --> 00:00:49,320
find you again.

14
00:00:49,640 --> 00:00:54,440
[Queen of Darkness]

15
00:00:54,880 --> 00:00:56,880
[Three years later]

16
00:00:57,120 --> 00:01:00,280
[M City, a Pacific Island Country]

17
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:07,856
Ye Ying.

18
00:01:07,880 --> 00:01:09,096
You sneaky woman.

19
00:01:09,120 --> 00:01:10,536
We finally caught you.

20
00:01:10,560 --> 00:01:13,056
Your Qingyun Gang messed with
the wrong people.

21
00:01:13,080 --> 00:01:14,096
Our boss said that

22
00:01:14,120 --> 00:01:15,240
you're all going down today!

23
00:01:16,160 --> 00:01:17,400
Nonsense talking.

24
00:01:23,240 --> 00:01:25,720
[Ye Ying, Young Lady of Qingyun Gang]

25
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:46,160
♪ I got fire in my veins ♪

26
00:01:46,720 --> 00:01:48,920
♪ I got matches burning up ♪

27
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:51,720
♪ We're in a fighting ♪

28
00:01:52,040 --> 00:01:53,960
♪ I'm gonna take it out ♪

29
00:01:54,240 --> 00:01:55,240
Inspector Huo.

30
00:01:55,720 --> 00:01:56,920
What do you mean by this?

31
00:01:57,480 --> 00:01:58,216
My Qingyun Gang.

32
00:01:58,240 --> 00:01:59,196
[Ye Hong, Leader of Qingyun Gang]
hasn't offended

33
00:01:59,220 --> 00:02:00,220
the police lately, huh?

34
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:08,840
Whether you have or not.

35
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:10,856
[Huo Xiao, Police Inspector]

36
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:12,160
Depends on my mood today.

37
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:30,720
Just say what you want.

38
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:31,920
Ye Hong,

39
00:02:32,720 --> 00:02:34,400
you know what I'm after.

40
00:02:35,320 --> 00:02:38,256
Either hand it over today

41
00:02:38,280 --> 00:02:39,280
or.

42
00:02:40,440 --> 00:02:42,640
Qingyun Gang disappears.

43
00:02:45,320 --> 00:02:48,896
I've done plenty of favors
for you all these years.

44
00:02:48,920 --> 00:02:51,800
And you still want to wipe me out.

45
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:57,200
Listen.

46
00:02:58,640 --> 00:03:00,240
The Qingyun Gang isn't pushovers either!

47
00:03:04,720 --> 00:03:06,160
So there's nothing more to say.

48
00:03:17,040 --> 00:03:19,296
Miss, why did you come back early?

49
00:03:19,320 --> 00:03:19,897
The boss told us

50
00:03:19,921 --> 00:03:21,000
to pick you up tonight.

51
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:23,240
I came back early to surprise Dad.

52
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:24,160
Where's my dad?

53
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:25,360
What's going on?

54
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:27,856
Inspector Huo and the boss
went to the rooftop.

55
00:03:27,880 --> 00:03:28,657
That man may want to
cause trouble again.

56
00:03:28,681 --> 00:03:29,920
And asks for some benefit.

57
00:03:30,080 --> 00:03:31,080
Which Inspector Huo?

58
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:32,800
Huo Xiao, Inspector Huo.

59
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:48,560
Dad!

60
00:03:51,880 --> 00:03:52,880
Dad!

61
00:03:53,440 --> 00:03:54,440
Dad!

62
00:03:55,440 --> 00:03:56,440
Dad.

63
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:04,400
Huo Xiao.

64
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:08,440
I'll kill you!

65
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:09,576
[Dr. LOGY Pathology Lab]

66
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:10,600
An Ning.

67
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:12,840
[Mrs. Song]
The Song family is worth billions.

68
00:04:13,040 --> 00:04:14,480
We need heirs.

69
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:16,776
[An Ning, 27, Not Pregnant]
What's the point of

70
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:17,536
marrying a barren wife like you?

71
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:18,560
Mom.

72
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:19,536
[An Ning] The doctor said there's nothing.

73
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:21,400
[Daughter-in-law of Song family]
wrong with me.

74
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:23,976
Watch your manners.

75
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,040
It's not your turn to talk
when elders are speaking.

76
00:04:26,280 --> 00:04:28,080
Such an ill-mannered child.

77
00:04:28,360 --> 00:04:29,257
Auntie.

78
00:04:29,281 --> 00:04:30,336
Please don't be upset.

79
00:04:30,360 --> 00:04:32,336
[Fang Yao, An Ning's friend]
An Ning's mother passed away early.

80
00:04:32,360 --> 00:04:34,216
And her father also left recently.

81
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:36,760
It's understandable
she doesn't know these rules.

82
00:04:38,760 --> 00:04:40,040
She's your daughter-in-law now.

83
00:04:40,320 --> 00:04:42,560
Your guidance will mean a lot to her.

84
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:50,696
Fang Yao is right.

85
00:04:50,720 --> 00:04:52,136
She came from an ordinary family.

86
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:53,240
No sense of proper manners.

87
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:55,320
I'll teach her some today.

88
00:04:55,960 --> 00:04:56,960
An Ning.

89
00:04:57,320 --> 00:04:58,880
Go get the soup.

90
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:11,360
Kneel.

91
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:22,536
Lift the soup above your head.

92
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:23,840
And bring it over on your knees.

93
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:29,056
Being a wife and daughter-in-law
in a wealthy family,

94
00:05:29,080 --> 00:05:31,840
the most important thing is
to contribute to the household.

95
00:05:32,760 --> 00:05:34,536
Since you can't bear children,

96
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:36,440
can't you at least
show respect to your in-laws?

97
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:42,017
An Ning.

98
00:05:42,041 --> 00:05:43,856
Just do as auntie says.

99
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:45,280
Your parents passed away early.

100
00:05:45,520 --> 00:05:47,456
Do you want people
to call you uneducated?

101
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:48,960
Or to badmouth your parents?

102
00:06:16,040 --> 00:06:17,536
You can't even handle
such a small thing!

103
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:18,616
All you do is embarrass the Song family.

104
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:19,680
What else can you even do?

105
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:36,480
Fang Yao!

106
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:38,720
You're my best friend.

107
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:40,760
How could you guys do this?

108
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:44,056
[Ti Cha, An Ning's husband]
What are you crying for?

109
00:06:44,080 --> 00:06:45,896
I'm not dead yet!

110
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:47,200
Get out of here, now!

111
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:49,280
Don't ruin

112
00:06:50,160 --> 00:06:51,480
my good moment.

113
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:53,456
An Ning.

114
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:55,216
This is your fault.

115
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:57,400
How could you mess up
your husband's mood?

116
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:01,120
You...

117
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:02,520
You

118
00:07:02,840 --> 00:07:04,360
I'll make you pay for this!

119
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:12,760
You dare hit me?

120
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:15,000
Get down on your knees!

121
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:16,897
I

122
00:07:16,921 --> 00:07:18,656
I'll finish you today!

123
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:20,136
A barren hen.

124
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:21,960
A jinx who brought misfortune
to your parents!

125
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:25,336
In bed, you're like a dead fish.

126
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:27,040
And now you want to tell me what to do?

127
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:30,560
Still crying, huh?

128
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:33,920
Tramp like you,
no one'd take even for free!

129
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:38,856
An Ning.

130
00:07:38,880 --> 00:07:40,856
Your face is all bruised up.

131
00:07:40,880 --> 00:07:42,120
Well,

132
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:43,960
shall I dab some medicine on you?

133
00:07:46,440 --> 00:07:47,440
Come here.

134
00:07:48,160 --> 00:07:49,160
Come on.

135
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:54,720
Go ahead.

136
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:01,576
Ti Cha.

137
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:04,136
Didn't you say An Ning
never makes a sound?

138
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:06,600
Doesn't she sound pretty when she does?

139
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:09,800
Not as nice as you do, though.

140
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:14,080
Look at her.

141
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:17,616
[Song Pa, An Ning's father-in-law]

142
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:19,160
She drove that car out?

143
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:23,216
The car was already tampered with.

144
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:25,240
She won't make it back today.

145
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:28,176
The An family's company
has long been mine.

146
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:29,616
[Brake system fault]
Leaving some shares to her daughter

147
00:08:29,640 --> 00:08:31,056
won't change a thing.

148
00:08:31,080 --> 00:08:34,120
It will all be mine eventually.

149
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:39,440
Huo Xiao.

150
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:41,120
I'm going to end you.

151
00:08:41,720 --> 00:08:42,840
For my father's sake.

152
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:57,160
[Hospital]

153
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:06,200
Who are you?

154
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:09,160
Why am I here?

155
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:12,200
An Ning.

156
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:14,000
Don't think playing dumb

157
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:17,040
will get you out of
the trouble from the car crash.

158
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:18,440
A car crash?

159
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:22,680
How did I get into a car crash?

160
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,200
My head hurts so much.

161
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,160
Why does my head hurt so bad?

162
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:32,456
Why can't I remember anything?

163
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:33,480
An Ning.

164
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:34,760
That's enough.

165
00:09:37,040 --> 00:09:38,040
An Ning?

166
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:40,360
Who's An Ning?

167
00:09:40,920 --> 00:09:42,416
An Ning is you.

168
00:09:42,440 --> 00:09:43,440
The useless waste.

169
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:45,600
Who are you?

170
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:47,640
How dare you call me a waste?

171
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:51,216
Because I'm your husband's mother.

172
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:52,336
Your mother-in-law.

173
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:54,160
How dare you talk back to me?

174
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:55,696
If I don't teach you a lesson today,

175
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:57,056
I've failed as your mother-in-law!

176
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:58,176
Running out in the middle of the night.

177
00:09:58,200 --> 00:09:59,296
And stirring up so much trouble.

178
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:00,976
Why not just end it once and for all?

179
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,000
I...

180
00:10:04,680 --> 00:10:05,680
You... you...

181
00:10:05,920 --> 00:10:06,496
Mom.

182
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:07,257
Mom! Mom! Mom.

183
00:10:07,281 --> 00:10:10,136
You poor girl with no family left.

184
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:11,896
You've really got some nerve, huh?

185
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:13,376
How dare you try to hit me!

186
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:15,800
Let... Let go of me!

187
00:10:17,880 --> 00:10:19,696
Mom. Mom. Mom.

188
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:20,656
Are you okay, Mom?

189
00:10:20,680 --> 00:10:21,680
Just drop dead!

190
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:31,160
Where did this crazy woman come from?

191
00:10:32,560 --> 00:10:33,936
If you lose control again,

192
00:10:33,960 --> 00:10:36,000
I won't mind breaking your other arm.

193
00:10:38,080 --> 00:10:39,080
Mom.

194
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:40,240
Are you okay, Mom?

195
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:43,177
You mean woman.

196
00:10:43,201 --> 00:10:45,336
You should take a look at yourself first.

197
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:46,297
Who do you think you are?

198
00:10:46,321 --> 00:10:47,816
Daring to hit my mom.

199
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:49,240
Well, I finally get it now.

200
00:10:49,880 --> 00:10:51,136
A spiteful mother-in-law

201
00:10:51,160 --> 00:10:52,480
and her clingy son.

202
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:55,056
I must've been blind to
fall for your messed-up family.

203
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:56,080
An Ning.

204
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:58,176
I used to treat you like a punching bag.

205
00:10:58,200 --> 00:10:59,920
You don't even dare to make a sound.

206
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:01,080
So what?

207
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:03,520
Did that car crash shake up
your whole personality?

208
00:11:03,680 --> 00:11:04,457
Now,

209
00:11:04,481 --> 00:11:06,576
get on your knees
and kowtow three times to me!

210
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:07,377
I'll

211
00:11:07,401 --> 00:11:09,960
let you keep serving the Song family!

212
00:11:13,120 --> 00:11:14,656
You perfectly exemplify

213
00:11:14,680 --> 00:11:15,776
what it means to be a brute.

214
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:17,216
All you do is insult women

215
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:18,640
to patch up your sad little pride.

216
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:20,880
Try being a decent person in this life.

217
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:22,216
In the next one,

218
00:11:22,240 --> 00:11:23,536
being a fly

219
00:11:23,560 --> 00:11:25,200
is the upper limit of your reincarnation!

220
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:27,536
You... What are you doing?

221
00:11:27,560 --> 00:11:29,520
Son! Son!

222
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:30,576
You...

223
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:31,177
Son!

224
00:11:31,201 --> 00:11:32,441
You're not An Ning - It hurts!

225
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:33,960
What do you mean?

226
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:35,257
Then who am I?

227
00:11:35,281 --> 00:11:36,536
Your words and actions

228
00:11:36,560 --> 00:11:38,160
don't match her at all.

229
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:39,257
So that question

230
00:11:39,281 --> 00:11:40,720
should be mine to ask you.

231
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:43,857
Mr. Song,

232
00:11:43,881 --> 00:11:44,976
after consulting with specialists,

233
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:47,056
we believe your daughter-in-law suffered
severe head trauma,

234
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:48,536
which caused retrograde amnesia.

235
00:11:48,560 --> 00:11:50,536
It might lead to
major personality changes.

236
00:11:50,560 --> 00:11:52,096
How long will it take for me to regain
my memory?

237
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:52,897
Hard to say.

238
00:11:52,921 --> 00:11:54,296
But familiar people and places

239
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:55,720
could help trigger your memory.

240
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:57,697
However,

241
00:11:57,721 --> 00:11:59,200
do either of your arms...

242
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:00,800
No need.

243
00:12:04,040 --> 00:12:05,640
I don't trust any of you.

244
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:09,280
Until my memory comes back,

245
00:12:09,760 --> 00:12:12,440
I'll request 24-hour police protection.

246
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:28,440
You've come just in time.

247
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:30,297
Since coming back with you,

248
00:12:30,321 --> 00:12:32,776
I realized all the wrongs
you've done to me before.

249
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:33,936
The police are on their way.

250
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:35,320
Please explain yourselves clearly.

251
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:10,420
♪ Mist coils around the sleeping forest ♪

252
00:13:10,890 --> 00:13:14,070
♪ Memories scattered
through cracks of darkness ♪

253
00:13:14,450 --> 00:13:17,920
♪ How to escape this real-feeling dream ♪

254
00:13:21,470 --> 00:13:24,730
♪ Lies reflect in water's gleam ♪

255
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:28,290
♪ Traces of existence
can never be erased ♪

256
00:13:28,580 --> 00:13:31,850
♪ How to find the self I can't reclaim ♪

257
00:13:34,170 --> 00:13:41,240
♪ Fly away, hear she says ♪

258
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:45,266
♪ She'll fly out from
thorns of woven lies ♪

259
00:13:45,290 --> 00:13:48,876
♪ Pierce the fog,
shatter this dream tonight ♪

260
00:13:48,900 --> 00:13:51,836
♪ Burn like fire ♪

